1
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:13,200
Hey.

2
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:18,600
Pong?

3
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:21,680
Are you alright now?

4
00:00:22,640 --> 00:00:26,200
Help me. Help… Help…

5
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:31,120
Please let me go.

6
00:00:32,479 --> 00:00:35,720
So, Soi and Pong are really dead?

7
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:41,520
My child… Where is my child?

8
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:43,080
Where is my child?

9
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:45,680
Let my child go.

10
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:48,280
Please let my child go. No! No!

11
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:17,880
Oh.

12
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:20,280
Why are you so startled?

13
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,520
Of course I'm startled.

14
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:22,960
Is something wrong?

15
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:26,640
Well, Somkid, the security guard,
said that yesterday,

16
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:29,880
you ran into Jirasin and had an argument.
What happened?

17
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,680
Kluay and I snuck into Grandma's office.

18
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:34,240
-Huh?
-We ran into Jirasin there.

19
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:36,640
-Huh?
-And not only that,

20
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:38,800
he secretly took photos of us.

21
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:39,840
-Don't say "Huh."
-Hey!

22
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,680
Mr. Arnon, don't worry.

23
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:47,400
Mr. Warat and I already met
Grandma and Sin earlier.

24
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:50,400
Sin didn't show any reaction.

25
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:53,320
I don't think he's holding a grudge.

26
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,320
-Impossible.
-Impossible.

27
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:59,880
I know you two don't trust Sin.

28
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:04,120
But if he's staying calm right now,
shouldn't we stay calm too?

29
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:07,800
If we overreact,
we'll look like the guilty ones.

30
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:11,320
Ms. Kluay has a point.

31
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:15,680
Why would Jirasin play the good guy?

32
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:18,800
So he can officially
become Grandma's adopted son sooner.

33
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:21,360
I don't think so.

34
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:25,880
Mrs. Wanee announced publicly
that she'd leave everything to you.

35
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:27,400
What would be left for him to take?

36
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:32,920
Let's pause this for a second.

37
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,520
Let's look at the photos
from yesterday first.

38
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,680
What? You had the photos
and didn't say anything?

39
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,480
You didn't ask.

40
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,960
If you were your sister, I'd smack you.

41
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,640
What photos do we have?

42
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:56,680
Wait. Stop.

43
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:00,760
Go back.

44
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:07,200
See that?

45
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:10,520
That woman at the back,

46
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,200
the one holding a child.

47
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:14,720
CROP

48
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:18,640
That's Ms. Ampha. Her face is clear.

49
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:23,600
Then the two on the other side

50
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,080
must be Pong and Soi.

51
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:33,000
Close it.

52
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:37,760
That's good, isn't it?

53
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:41,600
If Kluay and Mr. Warat find those two,
everything will unravel.

54
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:43,240
It's not that simple.

55
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,960
We'd have to check the foundation
handling unclaimed bodies,

56
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:49,600
verify relatives' DNA,
and compare the results.

57
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:51,640
Wow, that's complicated.

58
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:54,680
Oh, I got excited for nothing.

59
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:58,640
Oh, I'll go check the CCTV hard drive
for Mama Toi. She said

60
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:02,280
she wants footage of the guests who came
this morning for the birthday.

61
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:05,360
Mom said someone delivered something
by mistake, so she wants the footage.

62
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:07,760
Go ahead, Arnon.
I'll handle the technician.

63
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:10,400
But don't gossip.

64
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:33,000
Why are you so hungry?

65
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:36,960
I've never seen you eat this much.

66
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:41,520
This is my first meal
since yesterday evening.

67
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,440
Huh?

68
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:48,200
Don't say huh. Last night, I was about
to eat, you had an argument with Grandma.

69
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:51,840
Then late at night, things calmed down
and you dragged me to the office.

70
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:54,960
This morning,
when I tried to have breakfast,

71
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,840
you argued with Grandma again.

72
00:06:56,920 --> 00:07:01,120
So tell me.
When exactly was I supposed to eat?

73
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:02,920
Don't make excuses.

74
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:06,440
You could've had a slice of bread
or a sandwich.

75
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,240
Are you sure you're you

76
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:12,120
and not a hungry ghost possessing you?

77
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:15,440
Hey?

78
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:22,840
You startled me.

79
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:24,960
Kluay, you silly girl.

80
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:31,120
I'm full. I feel like
I've ascended to heaven.

81
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:34,080
If you're full, let's talk.

82
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:38,160
Are we going to speak to the maid
at Ameena's house

83
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:42,280
about DNA comparison
with the unclaimed bodies?

84
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:45,480
You're the one who has to go, not me.

85
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:49,120
What? How can I go alone? Come with me.

86
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:53,520
Not to Ameena's house. Absolutely not.

87
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:02,640
Oh? Why did you order more?
You said you were full.

88
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:04,840
I didn't order for myself.

89
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:10,400
Huh?

90
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:15,640
Hey, if you're going to do something,
consult me first.

91
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:18,560
If I told you,
you'd drag me to another restaurant.

92
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:22,320
Well, since it's ordered,
let's help them out.

93
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:25,480
Hey.

94
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:28,520
Why are you putting it here?
Put it over there.

95
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,200
They're sitting next to you.

96
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:41,960
Looks like they brought the whole village.

97
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,240
Hey.

98
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:50,440
Did you tease me?

99
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:53,800
And the two next to me
are not real either, right?

100
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:58,040
No, those two are real.

101
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,000
Hey.

102
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:06,720
What are you doing?

103
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:11,800
<i>The one who has been following you</i>

104
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:13,880
<i>was murdered.</i>

105
00:09:15,760 --> 00:09:17,680
The one who's been following me?

106
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:20,760
Kluay, stop it. This isn't funny.

107
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:23,520
Mr. Warat. Please continue.

108
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:27,920
<i>The killer has powerful occult abilities.</i>

109
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:31,400
<i>It's someone close to you. Be careful.</i>

110
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,400
Thank you so much.

111
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:45,080
Kluay, what are you doing?

112
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:49,400
Someone with occult power…

113
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:58,160
If the monitor doesn't turn on,

114
00:09:58,240 --> 00:10:01,720
we'll probably have to replace it,
like the technician said.

115
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:04,880
Let me check whether
the hard drive still works.

116
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,120
If I turn it on and it displays,

117
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:17,000
we won't need a new hard drive.

118
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:20,640
Good. That'll save money.

119
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:22,880
Give it a moment to set up.

120
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:29,800
The latest footage should be from
the birthday merit-making this morning.

121
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:32,200
Oh. That's good.

122
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:34,760
So many donors came in a row.

123
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,200
Ah. Here it is.

124
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,680
The footage

125
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:44,840
seems complete.

126
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:48,040
The hard drive isn't damaged, Mama Toi.

127
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:51,560
You're right. The footage is all here.

128
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:56,280
Right after the last group of guests left,
the camera shut off.

129
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:00,080
Here. This part.

130
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,440
Who are these two?

131
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:14,480
The last guests
who came for the merit-making.

132
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:19,400
Mama Toi,

133
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:22,920
is this man named Mr. Sarut?

134
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:25,280
I'm not sure.

135
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:27,480
He didn't want to disclose his name.

136
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:44,480
Focus, Kluay. Focus.

137
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,480
Someone close to me?

138
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:55,360
Yes. The spirits were repaying us
for feeding them by warning us.

139
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,960
I don't think they were lying.

140
00:11:57,560 --> 00:11:58,600
So what?

141
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,880
What do we do?

142
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:05,640
Meditate. I want to talk to Ms. Ampha.

143
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:08,600
She hasn't communicated in a long time.
Help me.

144
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:11,760
-What?
-Give me your hand.

145
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:13,520
-And meditate?
-Yeah.

146
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,040
Give me your hand.

147
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:21,440
Come on, come on.

148
00:12:23,520 --> 00:12:24,920
Close your eyes.

149
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:38,320
-You're cheating. You didn't close yours.
-Oh.

150
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:41,000
If I closed my eyes,
how would I know you're cheating?

151
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:43,320
Close your eyes. Now.

152
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:46,800
Close them. Close them.

153
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:49,160
Mr. Warat, close your eyes.

154
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:50,720
They're closed.

155
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:11,080
Ms. Ampha.

156
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:15,400
What happened to you? Who hurt you?

157
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:17,560
What's wrong with her?

158
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:19,400
Ms. Ampha.

159
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:25,400
<i>Your body will burn like fire.</i>

160
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:33,280
<i>Don't you dare fight me…</i>

161
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:37,600
<i>Ampha.</i>

162
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:44,320
Ms. Ampha?

163
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:48,080
Huh? What just happened?

164
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:03,400
How dare you
influence Mr. Rut to tear down this room?!

165
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:13,960
Aunt Nong.

166
00:14:18,040 --> 00:14:19,080
Aunt Nong.

167
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:22,320
-Aunt Nong.
-You're back, Sin?

168
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:28,480
Where did you sleep last night?
Why didn't you answer my calls?

169
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:33,880
Aunt Nong, your mouth…

170
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:35,120
Kluay.

171
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:38,280
Mom!

172
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:43,960
-I missed you.
-I missed you so much,

173
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:46,120
sweetheart.

174
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:51,320
Are you coming home now, Kluay?

175
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:55,800
The job's not done yet, Mom.

176
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:57,960
Oh? Really?

177
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:03,600
That makes me uneasy.

178
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:09,040
You're just one person.
How can you help that whole family?

179
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:13,080
That's what I was thinking too.
I don't know if I can handle it.

180
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:14,920
But I'll do my best.

181
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:20,440
Mom, I'm going to see Grandpa.
Maybe he'll have some answers.

182
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:24,200
Oh, perfect timing.
I was about to go see him too.

183
00:16:24,280 --> 00:16:25,960
I prepared lots of food.

184
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:28,800
Oh. Then I'll take it to him.

185
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:33,120
It all looks delicious.

186
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:50,600
You're here,
my little powerhouse granddaughter?

187
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:57,560
Hello, Grandpa. Did I wake you up?

188
00:16:58,760 --> 00:17:01,400
I wasn't asleep. It's called meditation.

189
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:04,280
Oh right, meditation.

190
00:17:04,359 --> 00:17:07,000
I just used the wrong word.

191
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:09,760
How could I not know you were meditating?

192
00:17:09,839 --> 00:17:12,000
I've seen you meditate since I was little.

193
00:17:12,079 --> 00:17:14,319
You haven't visited in a while.

194
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:17,000
Your mom said you've been busy.

195
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:22,000
Yes, very, very busy.

196
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,960
I feel bad.

197
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:31,960
What should I do, Grandpa?
How can I help Ms. Ampha?

198
00:17:33,840 --> 00:17:36,080
It looks like she's been attacked.

199
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:39,520
There are many dark practices
among wicked people.

200
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,240
She's under a harmful spell.

201
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:44,720
Oh.

202
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:49,400
Then what should I do?

203
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:57,800
What you've done so far is right.

204
00:17:57,880 --> 00:18:02,040
Love her more.
The power of love and compassion

205
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:03,520
will open the path for you.

206
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:06,360
Love her more?

207
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:07,400
Yes.

208
00:18:07,480 --> 00:18:11,640
True love is the purest power.

209
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:17,360
She's bound by a dark spell.

210
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:20,520
Her mouth is sealed so she cannot speak.

211
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:21,680
Oh.

212
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:25,000
That's right.
Ms. Ampha really can't speak.

213
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:27,240
Good that you know.

214
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:29,560
Her body is restrained by spells too.

215
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:31,840
It's pitiful.

216
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:35,720
The cycle she's trapped in is heavy.

217
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:42,080
So, can I really help her?

218
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:45,160
Now you're treating me
like a fortune-teller.

219
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:49,960
See? You're so busy reaching into
the future you forget the present.

220
00:18:51,080 --> 00:18:54,800
No, Grandpa.
It's called encouraging myself.

221
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:59,480
You've got all the answers.
No more questions.

222
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:02,920
No, Grandpa. I still have many questions.

223
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,120
Please,

224
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,200
just three more.

225
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:06,760
Two.

226
00:19:06,840 --> 00:19:09,200
One. Just one question.

227
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:12,880
One question only. Please tell my fortune.

228
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:18,040
Hello?

229
00:19:18,120 --> 00:19:22,240
Sorry. I just woke up.
I couldn't sleep well last night.

230
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:26,880
You're at the office already?
Okay, I'll be there soon.

231
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,040
Hello?

232
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:33,880
Is your psychiatrist friend still working?

233
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:37,160
<i>Yes, he's still at the same hospital.</i>

234
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:39,400
<i>Why? Is someone unwell?</i>

235
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:47,240
My aunt.

236
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:50,880
She's not doing well. I'm afraid

237
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:52,720
if we leave it, it'll get worse.

238
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:04,240
Wait, Sin.

239
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:08,880
Thanks for the birthday gift.

240
00:20:09,440 --> 00:20:10,640
What gift?

241
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:15,280
The birthday gift you had Nong pass to me.

242
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:22,600
You must've been fooled by Aunt Nong.

243
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:23,680
Hm?

244
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:29,520
-How could I buy you a birthday gift?
-Hm?

245
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:30,960
I don't even remember your birthday.

246
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:42,800
<i>Hey, Sin, come here.</i>

247
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:44,320
What is it?

248
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:47,080
Come talk to me. Why?

249
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:50,080
Why didn't you consult me
before talking to Uncle Rut?

250
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:51,360
About what?

251
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:53,000
Oh.

252
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:56,200
The birthday gift?
I told him I didn't buy it.

253
00:20:56,280 --> 00:20:58,480
If I lied, he wouldn't believe me anyway.

254
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:00,840
Is he crazy?
I almost ran him over the other day.

255
00:21:01,520 --> 00:21:03,800
Then make it better now.

256
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:06,120
Why fight with him?

257
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,880
He's moving you to the storage room,
you know?

258
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:11,000
Good. I'll renovate it.

259
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:13,160
Then you can stop messing
with those lowly things.

260
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:21,600
-Aunt Nong, well…
-Sin.

261
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:25,600
-Why did you insult me like that?
-I…

262
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:27,040
I'm sorry, Aunt Nong.

263
00:21:30,760 --> 00:21:32,200
I'm going to work now.

264
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:35,360
But tell Uncle Rut he can do
whatever he wants. I can live anywhere.

265
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:37,200
But I'll stay to take care of you.

266
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:50,560
One day, I'll throw you out of this house.

267
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:05,880
This is Mr. Sarut and his wife.

268
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:14,400
I don't get it.

269
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:19,040
Why would they
make merit at Baan Saeng Wan Mai?

270
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:23,240
And that's not all.

271
00:22:23,320 --> 00:22:26,720
There's another woman with the same name

272
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:29,520
as Mr. Sarut's wife.

273
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,280
-Anong?
-Yes.

274
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:38,360
She called
asking for the orphan list there.

275
00:22:39,320 --> 00:22:41,720
Som answered the call.

276
00:22:42,920 --> 00:22:44,960
Luckily, she didn't give any information.

277
00:22:45,040 --> 00:22:48,960
It's against the rules. It just makes Som
more worried about Ms. Kluay.

278
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:50,960
How is this…

279
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:54,080
connected to Kluay?

280
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:01,240
-Mr. Arnon.
-Yes?

281
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:03,040
How is this related to Kluay?

282
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:08,360
Mama Toi

283
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:11,920
asked me
to investigate Ms. Kluay's relatives.

284
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:16,200
I think this is serious.

285
00:23:16,840 --> 00:23:18,760
If it succeeds, great.

286
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:20,680
But if not,

287
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:24,400
I think Kluay will be devastated.

288
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:28,920
Mama Toi told me to investigate quietly,

289
00:23:30,120 --> 00:23:33,080
so whether I succeed or fail,

290
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:35,760
no one gets hurt or upset.

291
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:40,080
That's not right. Did you ask Kluay?

292
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:42,240
If she finds out,

293
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:46,680
I think she'll be upset.

294
00:23:48,280 --> 00:23:49,120
And…

295
00:23:49,840 --> 00:23:52,240
No, this doesn't work.
If it were me, I'd be furious.

296
00:23:52,840 --> 00:23:55,360
You're furious about everything. See?

297
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:59,600
Tell me. How are you investigating it?

298
00:23:59,680 --> 00:24:02,680
Every investigation
needs a starting point.

299
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:06,280
Maybe I can apply it to my own case.

300
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:10,160
Why am I being squeezed for information?

301
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:13,720
If you want Kluay to know, go ahead.

302
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:18,000
Hang up now. I'll tell you.

303
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:24,680
Ms. Kluay has worn an anklet
since childhood.

304
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:27,800
Huh? An anklet?

305
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:31,720
Yes. It's the only evidence we have.

306
00:24:43,840 --> 00:24:45,920
Is the new camera good, Mama Toi?

307
00:24:46,440 --> 00:24:48,040
The picture's quite sharp.

308
00:24:54,120 --> 00:24:55,360
<i>Who are these two?</i>

309
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:59,560
The last guests
who came for the merit-making.

310
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:00,960
Is this man

311
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:03,800
named Mr. Sarut?

312
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:08,640
TAXI METER

313
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:19,360
<i>My man sent this.</i>

314
00:25:27,280 --> 00:25:28,720
<i>Good.</i>

315
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:31,280
<i>Keep following her.</i>

316
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:35,080
<i>Maybe it's not that Waree girl.</i>
<i>You're overthinking.</i>

317
00:25:37,120 --> 00:25:39,160
<i>Who asked for your opinion?</i>

318
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:43,640
<i>Do as I say. Unless you want them</i>
<i>to drag you to jail.</i>

319
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:45,480
<i>Yes.</i>

320
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:47,880
Who were you talking to?

321
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:58,320
-I was talking to an old friend.
-Oh?

322
00:25:58,400 --> 00:25:59,680
You have friends?

323
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:02,080
Huh?

324
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,320
Give me your phone.

325
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:09,280
Now. Hand it over.

326
00:26:13,360 --> 00:26:14,240
Come on.

327
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:22,560
You've been acting suspicious.
Many times already. Come on.

328
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:25,840
Now.

329
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:35,160
You got away with it.

330
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:38,520
It's true. I've already sent it

331
00:26:39,280 --> 00:26:41,520
to compare the gold purity
and the gold era.

332
00:26:42,120 --> 00:26:45,840
Will that really tell us
who the anklet belongs to?

333
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:47,400
Not exactly.

334
00:26:47,480 --> 00:26:50,640
But from what I found,
it was probably made in Ban Thong.

335
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:55,480
If you find out anything,

336
00:26:56,720 --> 00:27:00,240
tell me. Don't keep it to yourself.

337
00:27:00,320 --> 00:27:04,640
You already have so much work.
Why would I keep it quiet?

338
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:07,600
I just want to help Kluay for once.

339
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:12,200
She's always helped me,
even when she didn't have to.

340
00:27:20,960 --> 00:27:22,160
Yes.

341
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:29,400
Thank you, Mr. Warat,

342
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:33,000
for agreeing to join the meeting
to evaluate my project.

343
00:27:33,800 --> 00:27:37,040
But that doesn't mean I'll approve it.

344
00:27:37,120 --> 00:27:39,680
Just having you attend

345
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:41,320
makes me happy enough.

346
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:42,480
Please.

347
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:44,800
Are you messing with me?

348
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:48,560
What are you gonna do with the photos
you secretly took of me and Kluay?

349
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:53,400
Oh. I already forgot about those photos.

350
00:27:56,800 --> 00:27:58,280
-Jirasin.
-Mr. Warat, well…

351
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:01,960
I think you shouldn't provoke him.

352
00:28:02,040 --> 00:28:05,280
I'm not provoking anyone.
I really forgot about them.

353
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:07,920
Or do you want me to recover them
even though I erased them?

354
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:10,720
You deleted them? Liar.

355
00:28:12,600 --> 00:28:14,560
Why don't you ever blame yourself?

356
00:28:21,560 --> 00:28:24,680
Oh. Is no one home?

357
00:28:24,760 --> 00:28:26,360
They all went to the mall.

358
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:29,800
Uh, your shirt…

359
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:35,440
Oh, it's fine. Thank you.

360
00:28:35,520 --> 00:28:36,520
Alright.

361
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:09,600
If you and Kluay hadn't caused trouble,

362
00:29:09,680 --> 00:29:11,560
would this have come back to you?

363
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:15,200
Mom, as I told you,

364
00:29:15,280 --> 00:29:17,760
I interfered in their matters.
It's my fault.

365
00:29:17,840 --> 00:29:18,800
You…

366
00:29:24,080 --> 00:29:26,840
We're about to have a meeting.

367
00:29:26,920 --> 00:29:30,400
Let's keep the atmosphere pleasant.

368
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:35,040
You heard him, Warat.

369
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:37,760
Let's go.

370
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:48,120
I didn't think
he could twist things like that.

371
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:52,760
It's fine. You've already prepared
your counterattack for the meeting.

372
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:58,600
He won't expect this move.

373
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:01,320
Let's go.

374
00:30:20,680 --> 00:30:23,280
What? Aunt Noi was hit by a car?

375
00:30:23,360 --> 00:30:24,440
Where is she?

376
00:30:24,520 --> 00:30:28,880
At the hospital, but she probably
won't survive. Ampha, prepare yourself.

377
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:33,200
Soi and I debated for a long time
whether to tell you.

378
00:30:33,280 --> 00:30:36,760
How could you not? She's my only relative.

379
00:30:36,840 --> 00:30:38,280
-Take me there.
-Uh, wait.

380
00:30:38,360 --> 00:30:40,920
What about Miss Waree?
She'll cry for her mother.

381
00:30:41,480 --> 00:30:42,320
I'll carry her myself.

382
00:30:54,960 --> 00:30:56,440
Wait. Where are you going?

383
00:30:59,720 --> 00:31:01,320
Who is Aunt Noi?

384
00:31:03,400 --> 00:31:04,880
Ms. Kluay, were you calling me?

385
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:09,880
Oh. No, it's nothing.

386
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:27,240
Who is this young lady?

387
00:31:35,040 --> 00:31:37,920
Som? Are you with Kluay?

388
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:41,160
Huh? She's not at the office yet?

389
00:31:42,520 --> 00:31:46,120
Yes. Kluay went to see Grandpa.

390
00:31:49,520 --> 00:31:53,280
Arnon told me
the man in the CCTV's name is Sarut,

391
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:55,480
and his wife's name is Anong.

392
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:57,880
Kluay and Mr. Warat
have been to their house before.

393
00:31:57,960 --> 00:32:00,080
Then why did they lie to me

394
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:02,720
and say that they'd never met Kluay?

395
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:04,440
What is going on?

396
00:32:04,520 --> 00:32:07,080
I'm worried.

397
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:10,600
I'm sorry I didn't tell you earlier.

398
00:32:10,680 --> 00:32:14,000
Seeing you rush over like this
makes me uneasy too.

399
00:32:14,080 --> 00:32:17,120
From now on, tell me everything.

400
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:19,080
We'll handle it together.

401
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:24,560
We don't know whether that couple
has good or bad intentions toward Kluay.

402
00:32:27,840 --> 00:32:30,920
Or maybe it's because…

403
00:32:33,960 --> 00:32:36,280
I already know everything.

404
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:38,640
About you investigating Kluay's family.

405
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:42,080
Oh, Mr. Arnon…

406
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:44,320
Don't blame him.

407
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:46,240
I made him tell me.

408
00:32:47,040 --> 00:32:49,240
You understand me, don't you?

409
00:32:50,080 --> 00:32:52,120
It wouldn't be fair to Kluay

410
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:55,120
if we didn't help her
find out about her family

411
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:57,680
when we have a way.

412
00:32:59,280 --> 00:33:02,760
Yes. I understand now.

413
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:08,160
Mom, hello.

414
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:11,840
Why didn't you tell me
you planned to meet?

415
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:17,320
I had sudden business nearby.

416
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:20,400
Did you change your shirt?

417
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:23,720
Grandpa said you spilled food on it.

418
00:33:23,800 --> 00:33:26,480
Yes. My clumsiness.

419
00:33:26,560 --> 00:33:29,520
At first, I was going to borrow
Grandpa's white outfit,

420
00:33:29,600 --> 00:33:32,120
-but that would've been strange.
-Hey.

421
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:35,080
Kluay, wherever you go,

422
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:37,320
take care of yourself.

423
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:42,480
Once you're done helping Warat,
come home. I'm worried.

424
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:45,640
And why do you look so pale?

425
00:33:45,720 --> 00:33:47,360
Are you okay?

426
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:54,680
Same thing as before.
But this time, it's intense.

427
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:58,400
Oh, are you trying to handle both
the worldly and spiritual realms at once?

428
00:33:58,480 --> 00:33:59,720
You're taking it all on?

429
00:34:00,960 --> 00:34:04,240
Hey. Is this really the time to joke?

430
00:34:04,320 --> 00:34:05,680
Kluay,

431
00:34:05,760 --> 00:34:08,679
-what happened? Tell me.
-Mm.

432
00:34:09,480 --> 00:34:12,159
I'm not sure how to start.

433
00:34:12,239 --> 00:34:15,960
But can I eat first? I need to recharge.

434
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:25,440
KAEW

435
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:30,280
All messages were deleted

436
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:32,280
except the latest one.

437
00:34:33,199 --> 00:34:35,960
I told you I don't know how to use it.

438
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:38,440
The system deleted them on its own.

439
00:34:38,520 --> 00:34:40,560
I didn't do anything.

440
00:34:41,199 --> 00:34:43,199
You can make excuses all you want.

441
00:34:43,280 --> 00:34:47,360
But the only one
who knows the truth is you.

442
00:34:47,440 --> 00:34:49,239
I swear

443
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:52,280
I had no bad intentions.

444
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:56,960
I was talking to Kaew because I suspected

445
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:01,480
Kluay and Waree, Ms. Ampha's daughter,
might be the same person.

446
00:35:02,680 --> 00:35:05,840
-That means…
-What nonsense are you talking about?

447
00:35:06,680 --> 00:35:07,840
Stop it.

448
00:35:09,480 --> 00:35:13,240
Ampha and Wichan's child
died with Pong and Soi.

449
00:35:13,320 --> 00:35:16,320
You confirmed you saw the three bodies.

450
00:35:16,400 --> 00:35:17,480
Don't you remember?

451
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:39,280
Don't say anything yet.

452
00:35:40,040 --> 00:35:44,040
I'm just glad you've woken up.

453
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:49,880
What about… Warat?

454
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:52,280
-Mr. Warat?
-Yes.

455
00:35:53,040 --> 00:35:54,640
He's okay.

456
00:35:58,160 --> 00:36:00,760
Mr. Wichan entrusted him

457
00:36:00,840 --> 00:36:04,400
to Ms. Ampha for a while. But…

458
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:07,320
Right now…

459
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:11,080
Not anymore.

460
00:36:14,480 --> 00:36:15,480
Why?

461
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:20,160
Ms. Ampha and her daughter…

462
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:21,080
Hm?

463
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:24,040
They're dead.

464
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:30,520
That girl Waree

465
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:34,160
died in a car accident

466
00:36:34,240 --> 00:36:37,520
with Pong and Soi.

467
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:41,960
And…

468
00:36:42,040 --> 00:36:45,280
Ms. Ampha disappeared.

469
00:36:50,320 --> 00:36:52,240
While you were in surgery,

470
00:36:53,200 --> 00:36:57,320
so many terrible things happened.

471
00:37:03,560 --> 00:37:04,840
But at least…

472
00:37:07,360 --> 00:37:09,960
At least Mr. Warat

473
00:37:10,840 --> 00:37:14,480
will become
the second heir of the Vanich family

474
00:37:14,560 --> 00:37:16,200
after Mr. Wichan.

475
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:19,520
Then why are you worried about Kluay?

476
00:37:21,160 --> 00:37:22,200
I just…

477
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:25,480
Don't make me
lose more trust in you, Anong.

478
00:37:28,280 --> 00:37:31,800
What exactly are you planning?

479
00:37:35,240 --> 00:37:36,600
You're tying Vanich's hands

480
00:37:36,680 --> 00:37:38,960
and forcing us
to accept your deal, aren't you?

481
00:37:39,040 --> 00:37:41,160
What does this mean, Sin?

482
00:37:41,240 --> 00:37:42,360
NEXT EPISODE

483
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:46,640
<i>No matter what happens,</i>
<i>we'll always be sisters, right?</i>

484
00:37:46,720 --> 00:37:50,200
Did I make a mistake
by looking into Kluay's background?

485
00:37:50,280 --> 00:37:52,400
What exactly do you want from me? Tell me.

486
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:54,520
Don't speak to me like that.

487
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:56,200
What right do you have to order me around?

488
00:37:57,200 --> 00:37:58,640
<i>What exactly are they after?</i>

489
00:37:58,720 --> 00:38:01,440
<i>Why did he go</i>
<i>into the document storage room?</i>

490
00:38:03,840 --> 00:38:05,120
Who sent you?

491
00:38:05,880 --> 00:38:07,200
<i>Go where you belong.</i>

492
00:38:07,280 --> 00:38:09,440
<i>Ghosts should stay with ghosts.</i>
<i>Stop meddling with the living.</i>

493
00:38:12,800 --> 00:38:13,680
<i>Chatchai just called.</i>

494
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:17,320
Sin…

495
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:19,520
What happened to him?

496
00:38:20,520 --> 00:38:21,600
This is getting out of hand.

497
00:38:22,200 --> 00:38:24,720
Make sure the police investigation
doesn't lead back to me.

498
00:40:47,360 --> 00:40:49,880
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
